EdgeCase.desc: The test vector contains an edge case public key.

LowOrderPublicKey.desc: The public key has a low order. Some implementations reject such keys during key validation.

PrivateKeyNotNormalized.desc: The private key is not normalized. Decoding of such keys changes some bits of the key according to the DecodeScalar function defined in RFC 7748.

Pseudorandom.desc: The test vector has been generated pseudorandomly.

PublicKeyNotNormalized.desc: The public key is not normalized. The behaviour of such keys (if accepted) is well defined. RFC 7748 requires that the leading bits of the public key are ignored during decoding.

SharedZero.desc: The shared secret is all zero. This case is described in Section 6.1 of RFC 7748. Rejecting such shared secrets is optional. The reason for this check is that it helps to prevent attacks with low order points.

Special.desc: The values in the test vector have been computed so that XDH computation encounters a special case. Such values check for arithmetic errors.

SpecialSharedSecret.desc: The test vector contains values that generate an edge case shared secret. The purpose of this test vector is to check for arithmetic errors.
